<p>I create an Excel sheet with Apache POI using another sheet as template. Now I want to JUnit test if the result is correct. For checking the content, I have a simple String based solution. But, since I generate alternating rows from the template sheet, I also want to check if the cell styles of the resulting sheet are as expected. I give you a snippet of the desired check</p>  <pre><code>    List&lt;Row&gt; templateRowPair = // as input;     assertThat("template row count", templateRowPair.size(), is(equalTo(2)));      int firstReplacedRow = // as input;     int lastReplacedRow = // as input;     int replacedRows = lastReplacedRow - firstReplacedRow + 1;      for (int i = 0; i &lt; replacedRows; i++) {         int resultRowNum = firstReplacedRow + i;         Row generatedRow = generatedSheet.getRow(resultRowNum);         assertThat("replaced row", generatedRow, is(notNullValue()));         int templateRowIndex = i % 2;         Row templateRow = templateRowPair.get(templateRowIndex);         assertThat("template row", templateRow, is(notNullValue()));         compareRowStyle(templateRow, generatedRow);     } </code></pre>  <p>And here the method for comparing the cell styles:</p>  <pre><code>private void compareRowStyle(Row templateRow, Row generatedRow) {     // compare complete row style     CellStyle templateRowStyle = templateRow.getRowStyle();     CellStyle generatedRowStyle = generatedRow.getRowStyle();     if (templateRowStyle == null) {         assertThat("row style", generatedRowStyle , is(nullValue()));     } else {         assertThat("row style", generatedRowStyle , is(equalTo(templateRowStyle)));     }      // compare styles cell by cell     int cellIndex = 0;     Iterator&lt;Cell&gt; templateCellIterator = templateRow.cellIterator();     while (templateCellIterator.hasNext()) {         Cell templateCell = (Cell) templateCellIterator.next();         Cell generatedCell = generatedRow.getCell(cellIndex);         CellStyle templateCellStyle = templateCell.getCellStyle();         CellStyle generatedCellStyle = generatedCell.getCellStyle();         assertThat("cell style", generatedCellStyle, is(equalTo(templateCellStyle)));         cellIndex++;     } } </code></pre>  <p>I found this: <a href="https://github.com/tobyweston/simple-excel" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/tobyweston/simple-excel</a> But the documentation says that cells are compared regardless their cell styles. I want to avoid implementing a new matcher (hierarchy) in case there is already one.</p>